imdb.plot outline: Comedians may be funny onstage, but are they fun to live with? "Living with Funny" explores the unique relationships between several aspiring comedians and their significant others. These comedians often encounter tough crowds on tour, but some of their harshest critics are their wives, girlfriends, family and friends. These important people suffer through every bad joke and support their loved ones at decidedly unfunny moments. Comedians may get the laughs from the crowd, but can they win over those at home?
imdb.title: Living with Funny
plot: The curtain is lifted on the personal lives of Hollywood's up-and-coming comedians as we see what happens when they drop the mic and come home.
